{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nTurn on the cross-ticket overlap detector (epic only-crave-art) for THIS project by\nsetting `verify.overlap_enabled = true` in the tracked project config `rebar.toml`.\nThe feature's code shipped and is tested but ships gated OFF by default; this flips the\nflag on so plan-review runs the advisory store-wide overlap step and surfaces `overlap[]`\nsuggestions.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `rebar.toml` `[verify]` section sets `overlap_enabled = true` with an explanatory comment.\n- [ ] No OTHER config key changes: `git diff rebar.toml` shows only the added\n      `overlap_enabled` line + its comment block.\n- [ ] The file still parses:\n      `python -c \"import tomllib; tomllib.load(open('rebar.toml','rb'))\"` exits 0.\n- [ ] The local build reads the flag as true (not stale-global):\n      `python -c \"from rebar.config import load_config; assert load_config('.').verify.overlap_enabled is True\"`\n      exits 0.\n- [ ] The overlap step executes end-to-end, proven by a structured assertion on the verdict.\n      `rebar review-plan` emits JSON by default (flag is `--output json` / `-o json`; there is\n      no `--json` flag):\n      `rebar review-plan ade2-8c73-e010-491d --output json | python -c \"import sys,json; v=json.load(sys.stdin); assert 'overlap' in v, v\"`\n      exits 0 (an empty `overlap: []` is expected until digests are enriched — the point is the\n      key is PRESENT, proving the step ran and the flag is wired, not stale-global).\n- [ ] Commit references this ticket (rebar-ticket trailer) and passes `make lint`.\n- [ ] Change lands on `main` through Gerrit (LLM-Review +1 and Verified +1).\n\n## Scope\n\n- **`rebar.toml` only — a one-key config flip, no code change.** It does not add, remove, or\n  alter any source; it activates behavior in code paths that already shipped and are already\n  covered by the epic's test suite (`tests/unit/test_plan_review_overlap.py`,\n  `tests/unit/test_enrich_drain.py`, etc.). `rebar.toml` is the tracked, git-committed project\n  config (preferred by config discovery over the git-ignored `.rebar/config.conf`), so the flag\n  is persistent and shared for all contributors without per-machine env-var setup. Rollback is\n  setting it back to false.\n\n## Behavioral activation — the flag gates TWO paths (both already tested)\n\nFlipping `overlap_enabled` on is a config-only change but it ACTIVATES two independent,\nalready-shipped code paths. Naming both so the behavioral consequence and its controls are explicit:\n\n1. **Plan-review overlap step** (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/`): the advisory two-stage\n   retrieve-then-rerank pass that populates `overlap[]` on the verdict. **Advisory only —\n   never blocks a claim or close.**\n2. **Opportunistic enrichment drain** (`src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py::maybe_drain`, gated on the\n   same `verify.overlap_enabled` check, invoked from the ticket write paths in\n   `_store/event_append.py` and `_store/push.py`): asynchronously builds the BM25F digests\n   stage-1 retrieval needs. So an ordinary `rebar` ticket write MAY now opportunistically trigger\n   LLM enrichment.\n\n**Mitigation / bounding (why path #2 is safe to enable):** the drain is best-effort and\n**can never fail a write** (`maybe_drain` swallows all exceptions); it only fires when there is\nsoaked + lease-eligible work, is bounded by the `[tool.rebar.llm] overlap_drain*` tunables\n(soak-min, lease-ttl, drain-batch, gate-budget), and — crucially — is **independently\ndisableable**: set `overlap_drain = \"off\"` under `[tool.rebar.llm]` to get plan-review overlap\nWITHOUT any write-path enrichment (default is `async`; `always` runs it inline for tests/CI).\nVerification of path #2's bounding/never-fails behavior is the epic's existing\n`tests/unit/test_enrich_drain.py` (an end-to-end drain-fire AC is intentionally NOT added here —\nthis ticket changes no code, only enables already-tested paths). Rollback\n(`overlap_enabled = false`) disables BOTH paths together."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783685595108483001,"uuid":"82324131-15d9-4a1f-9fcc-4c74029ef0fe"}